          <msContents>
            <summary>A Turkish translation of the <title xml:lang="fa-Latn-x-lc">Manāqib-i
                thawāqib</title>, (‘Virtues of the Eminent’), which is an abridgement by <persName
                xml:lang="fa-Latn-x-lc" key="">ʿAbd al-Wahhāb ibn Muḥammad Sabūnī
                al-Ḥamdānī</persName> of <title xml:lang="fa-Latn-x-lc">Manāqib al-ʿĀrifīn
                wa-murātib al-Kāshifīn</title>, a Persian work by <persName xml:lang="fa-Latn-x-lc"
                key="person_93291249">Aflākī, Shams al-Dīn Aḥmad, -1360</persName>. It contains
              a series of biographical panegyrics on various eminent Muslim saints and learned men. </summary>
            <msItem xml:id="R_13_1-item1">
              <author key="person_113381455">
                <persName xml:lang="ota-Latn-x-lc" type="supplied">Darvīsh Maḥmūd</persName>
                <persName xml:lang="ota">درويش محمود </persName>
              </author>
              <title xml:lang="ota-Latn-x-lc">Tarjumah-i manāqib-i s̲awāqib</title>

              <title xml:lang="ota">ترجمه مناقب ثواقب</title>


              <note>The present copy is dedicated to Sultan Murād Khān, and is interspersed with
                quotations from Persian poets. It is divided into nine chapters. </note>


              <listBibl>
                <bibl>
                  <ref
                    target="http://www.lib.cam.ac.uk/arabic_catalogues/browne1922/view.php?id=127"
